Shish taouk (Arabic: شيش طاووق‎; Hebrew: שישליק עוף‎; Turkish: şiş tavuk or tavuk şiş; Azerbaijani: toyuq kababı) is a traditional marinated chicken shish kebab of Middle Eastern cuisine. It is widely eaten in Turkey, Azerbaijan, Lebanon, Egypt, Jordan, Syria, Iraq, and Israel. A similar dish in Persian cuisine is the traditional jujeh kabab. It is also served in kebab houses in many cities around the world.
